If the EXECUTION PLAN declares `work_units` or `parallel_plan`, dispatch your own sub-agents to carry out the parallel work in dependency order within each unit's `allowed_directories`; if your runtime has no sub-agents, execute the same units sequentially in `unit_id` order. Ralph Workflow exposes no coordination command for plan work — dispatch is entirely your job. Even without declared work units, you may fan out read-only sub-agents for information gathering and run independent, non-overlapping steps concurrently; never let two sub-agents edit the same file.

